The cyclic voltammograms of DMCCE-GQDs were recorded at different sweep rates (from 10 to 350mVs−1) in the presence of 0.5mM Zlp (Fig. 5
                        ). Inset (A) in Fig. 5 illustrates that the oxidation peak currents (Ip) against the square of scan rates are linear for scan rates of 10–350mVs−1 and the linear regression equation is calculated as Ipa (μA)=3.57ν (mVs−1)+3.41 (R2
                        =0.95). This result emphasizes that the electrode reaction is controlled by mass transfer diffusion which is an appropriate behavior for quantitative analytical applications.
